options(digits=3)
set.seed(1)
mean.seq=function(x){
  n=length(x)
  sum=0
  n2=0
  for (i in 1:n){
    newx=i*x[i]
    sum=sum+newx
    n2=n2+i
  }
  return(sum/n2)
}
mean.seq2=function(x){
  n=length(x)
  sum(x*(1:n))/sum(1:n)
}
y1=rep(NA,1000)
y2=rep(NA,1000)

\(\hat{\theta}\)

.

\[ \hat{\theta}=\bar{X} \] \[\sqrt{E(\hat{\theta}-E(\hat{\theta}))^2}=\sqrt {E(\bar{X}-\mu)^2}=\sqrt{\sigma^2/N}=\sigma/\sqrt{N}\]

\(\sigma\) . \(\sigma\) \(s\) \(\bar{X}\) .

\[ SE(\bar{X}) =s/\sqrt{N}\qquad s=\sqrt{\frac{\sum_i X_i-\bar{X}}{N-1}}\] \(SE(\hat{\theta})\) \(\hat{SE(\theta)}\) . \(SE(\hat{\theta})\) .

is.even=function(x) return(!x%%2)#  (2   0 TRUE)
var.p=function(x){
  return(sum((x-mean(x))^2)/(length(x)))
}

p.even=function(x, s.size=3){
  return(sum(is.even(x))/s.size)
}

  1. : \(\theta\) \(100(1-\alpha)\)%

\[ P(\theta_L < \theta < \theta_U) = 1- \alpha\] \(\alpha=0.01\) : 99% \(\alpha=0.05\) : 95%

  1. : 100 \(100(1-\alpha)\) \(\theta\)

  2. 3.1. () \[ X_i \sim N(\mu,\sigma^2) \] \[ Z=\frac{\bar{X}-\mu}{\sigma/\sqrt{N}}\sim N(0,1)\] \[ P(-z_{\alpha/2}<Z<z_{\alpha/2})=1-\alpha =0.95\] \[ 2\times P(Z<-z_{\alpha/2})=0.05\]

\[ P(Z<-z_{\alpha/2})=0.025\rightarrow z_{\alpha/2}=1.96\]

\[P\left[-1.96 <\frac{\bar{X}-\mu}{\sigma/\sqrt{N}}<1.96\right] = 95\%\]

\[P\left[\bar{X}-1.96\sigma/\sqrt{N} <\mu<\bar{X}+1.96\sigma/\sqrt{N}\right] = 95\%\]

\[ (\bar{X}-1.96\sigma/\sqrt{N}, \bar{X}+1.96\sigma/\sqrt{N})\]

set.seed(9)
n=10
x=1:100
y=seq(-3,3,by=0.01)

smps=matrix(rnorm(n*length(x)),ncol=n)
xbar=apply(smps,1,mean)
se=1/sqrt(10)
alpha=0.05
z=qnorm(1-alpha/2)
ll=xbar-z*se
ul=xbar+z*se

plot(y,type="n",xlab="trial",ylab="z",main="95% CI", xlim=c(1,100),ylim=c(-1.5, 1.5),cex.lab=1.8)
abline(h=0,col="red",lty=2)
l.c=rep(NA,length(x))
l.c=ifelse(ll*ul>0,"red","black")
arrows(1:length(x),ll,1:length(x),ul,code=3,angle=90,length=0.02,col=l.c,lwd=1.5)

3.2. (t )

\[ T=\frac{\bar{X}-\mu}{s/\sqrt{N}}\sim t(N-1)\]

\[ P(-t_{\alpha/2,n-1}<T<t_{\alpha/2,n-1})=1-\alpha =0.95\] \[ 2\times P(T<-t_{\alpha/2,n-1})=0.05\] \[ P(T<-t_{\alpha/2,n-1})=0.025\rightarrow t_{\alpha/2,n-1}=2.78\qquad (N=5) \]

\[P\left[\bar{X}-2.78\times s/\sqrt{N} <\mu<\bar{X}+2.78\times s/\sqrt{N}\right] = 95\%\]

\[ (\bar{X}-2.78s/\sqrt{N}, \bar{X}+2.78s/\sqrt{N})\]

ci.t=function(x,alpha=0.05){
  n=length(x)
  m=mean(x)
  s=sd(x)
  t=-qt((alpha/2),df=n-1)
  #t=-qt(1-(alpha/2),df=n-1)
  ll=m-t*(s/sqrt(n))
  ul=m+t*(s/sqrt(n))
  ci=c(1-alpha,ll,m,ul)
  names(ci)=c("Confidence level","Lower limit","Mean","Upper limit")
  return(ci)
}

smp=c(520,498,481,512,515,542,520,518,527,526)
